Defendant Yolanda A Lawson appeared in court, Attorney Craig Gericke appeared in court for Yolanda A Lawson.  Attorney Emily Hynek appeared in court for the State of Wisconsin. Panel sworn in by clerk. Judge reads beginning jury instructions. 10:20 AM State gives opening statement. 10:26 AM Defense gives opening statement.  State calls witness M.Y., sworn in. States name and address. Testifies to incident. State questions witness.  Record reflects witness identifies defendant. Atty Gericke cross examines witness. State objects to line of questioning- overruled.  Continues. State objects to line of questioning- sustained. Continues. Objection calls for speculation. Continues. State redirects. No re-cross. State calls witness A.S., sworn in, testifies to incident. States name, address and employment. Atty Gericke cross examines witness. Atty Gericke approaches witness with a copy of her statement from incident. State redirects witness. Record reflects witness identifies defendant. Atty Gericke re-crosses. State calls witness B.M., sworn in, testifies to incident. States name, address and employment. Objection to line of questioning. Continues. Atty Gericke cross examines witness. No redirect. Break at 11:43 AM. Court trial resumes at 12:30 PM.  Jurors brought back in at 12:31 PM. State calls witness P.M. sworn in, testifies to incident. States name, address of where incident occurred. Must be 18 years and valid driver license to dance just the venue not the boss of the dancers. required to follow guidelines. Is called out regarding money being stolen. Searched premises and went through the belongings of the two dancers and septic found the paper bank envelope in the septic. Atty Gericke cross examines witness. There is a sheet the dancers sign after they dance with the amount of money they received in tips and the venue holds the money until the end. Atty Gericke approaches witness with a copy of his statement for his review regarding what bank the money envelope is from. State objects to line of questioning- overruled. Continues. State objects to line of questioning, speculation. Sustained. No redirect. State calls Deputy Radaj sworn in, states name, employed with the Jackson County Sheriff's Dept.; testifies.  The officer questioned the two dancers. Defendant had a private conversation with her friend.  He did not perform a physical search on the defendant.  Atty Gericke cross examines witness.  State objects to line of questioning- overruled. Continues. He did not arrest the defendant. State been asked many times- overruled. No redirect. Witness reserved for possible rebuttal. Jury exits courtroom at 1:32 PM.  Atty Gericke asks for a directed verdict there is no money or verification .  State disagrees testimony is evidence. Jury can make a determination to court denies motion.  State rests. Court recess at 1:34pm. Back on the record at 1:45PM. Atty Gericke defendant wishes to testify. Judge goes over her rights, defendant had a question for her attorney. Off the record at 1:46PM. Back on the record at 1:49PM Judge finishes going over the defendant's rights. Defendant still wishes to testify. 1:51PM Jury brought back into the courtroom. Defense calls the defendant to testify.  Defendant sworn in, testifies. States name, address and age at the time of the incident. Had previously been to the club before this incident with another dancer. States she was not paid for the that night in question. State objects calls for speculation, Overruled. Continues. Was called over by her dancer friend and was introduced to M.Y. told her friend it was time to go end of the night. She went to the dressing room and starting gathering her items and her friend followed shortly and bar manager shortly behind her accusing the two of stealing money. She allowed them to look through her belongings. She stated she told the officer she flushed the money so they could go home. Atty Hynek cross examines defendant. Defense objects to line of questioning. Jurors taken out of the court room. Court the way Atty Hynek is asking the question calls for speculation. The last question is to be stricken. Jurors brought back into the courtroom at 2:13 PM. Atty Hynek continues to question the defendant. No redirect. No other witnesses for defense. Defense rests.  No rebuttal from the state. State releases witness Deputy Radaj. Jurors are taken out of the courtroom at 2:17PM.  No motions from either party. Jury instruction discussion, #270 stricken from jury instruction. no expert testimony.  Defendant's previous convictions stricken. Take out #315 defendant did testify. Jury instructions approved. Jurors return to the courtroom 2:31 PM. Judge beings final jury instructions.  2:42PM     State gives closing argument. 2:48PM Defense gives closing argument. Rebuttal by the State. Final jury instructions given. Alternate is excused. Bailiff's sworn by clerk. Jury out to deliberate at 3:05PM. No objections as to the instructions read to the jury. Court recesses at 3:07PM. 4:55PM jury has a verdict. Judge reads verdict. Count 1- Not Guilty. No request for polling jurors. Court accepts the not guilty verdict, dismissed.

8:58AM Defendant Yolanda A Lawson appeared in court, Attorney Craig Gericke appeared in court for Yolanda A Lawson.  Attorney Emily Hynek appeared in court for the State of Wisconsin. Clerk swears in entire panel.  Voir dire begins at 9:00AM. Jury selection is completed at 9:50AM.
Remaining jurors excused.

8:31 AM Defendant Yolanda A Lawson in court.  Attorney Emily Hynek in court for State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Craig Gericke in court for Yolanda A Lawson. Review pretrials. Attorney Hynek states offer previously presented. Defendant does not accept offer.  Court satisfied defendant wishes to proceed with trial. State in compliance with victim notice. 
Attorney Gericke files a motion in limine today, brings up issue regarding a witness, discussion. State has no objection. Court grants motion in limine. Court instructs DAs office to advise any witnesses not to discuss or anything relating to the issue or anything in that fashion.  Court orders counsel to instruct witnesses if any sequestrations. No objections to drafted jury instructions.
Subpoena served on B.M to appear 3/23-3/24 JT
Subpoena served on AS to appear 3.23-3.24 JT
Subpoena served on MY to appear 3-23-24 JT

9:58 AM Defendant Yolanda A Lawson appeared by video, Attorney Craig Gericke appeared by video for Yolanda A Lawson, Attorney Emily Hynek appeared in court for State of Wisconsin. State in compliance with victim rights. Defendants impeachment motion addressed. State responds to the correct witness. Defense questions, asking for 12 answers (typo on his filed document) defense states motion, asking paragraph 12 not be counted, paragraph 8 be counted. State responds. Court - 13 should be counted, court concurs answer should be 12. 
Defendant motion in limine - no objection to court granting to all of motions. Victim has right to be in court room. 
States motion in limine - Defense asking for 0. State objects. Hennepin County dropped to a misdemeanor . Court satisfied there is a misdemeanor conviction, should be counted. Defendant should answer yes one time if asked if convicted of a crime.  No other objections to the other motions. Defense has no objection to proposed jury instructions. Court grants states other motions in limine.  
State recites previous offer to defendant. Defendant rejects the offers. Trial to proceed, starting at 8:30.
